50|$|Selectrix decoders have an <b>automatic</b> <b>brake</b> <b>function</b> {{which is}} {{activated}} when a decoder detects an asymmetrical track SX signal (this {{can be accomplished}} with a single diode used as a rectifier). This feature {{can be used to}} stop trains in front of a red signal automatically, for instance.|$|R
